cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing large networks and extracting roles within them. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a low rank iterative scheme for approximating the similarity measure. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves clustering and similarity measures. It may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for computing pairwise node similarity. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with analyzing flow patterns within a network.
